      "writtenOn": "2020-02-21T00:40:33Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It was just because my vim and go-fmt didn\u0027t agree with each other for the indent style.\n\nMy vim changes the indent\nfrom\nreturn fmt.Sprintf(\"...\",\n    invID, ....)\n\nto\nreturn fmt.Sprint(\"...\",\ninvID, ....)\n\nand go-fmt changes it back in the other way.\n\nI acknowledge that go-fmt is the official tool for go-lang indentations, but here are  alternatives that both vim and go-fmt agree with each other.(and I chose the last one)\n\n```\n// (1)\nreturn fmt.Sprintf(\n    \"invocation/%s/...\", invID, ...)\n\n// (2)\nreturn fmt.Sprintf(\n    \"invocations/%s/...\", invID, ...,\n)\n\n// (3)\ntestID \u003d url.PathEscape(...)\nreturn fmt.Sprintf(...)\n```\n\nNow, I changed it to (2). Let me if you have different opinions. I\u0027m happy to change it back to the original.",
      "parentUuid": "a187fdfa_5c287ff0",
      "revId": "4ab4890dd5d06707973e9bb86fc73a7332c4339c",
